    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-30T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="713"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.6511/132: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-30T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 30, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>278. Your 425, August 26, 3 p.m.<note n="44" xml:id="d713fn1">Not printed; the
                        Ambassador in Brazil asked for information as to the progress of steel plant
                        negotiations (832.6511/133).</note> Steel Commission has had a number of
                    conversations with Jesse Jones and Warren Pierson, and with various private
                    companies. Delay in definite action is due principally to fact that Congress has
                    not yet passed Bill authorizing 500 million dollar increase for Export-Import
                    Bank and removing 20 million dollar limitation. The Department and Jones and
                    Pierson are making every effort to push Bill and it is expected it will be acted
                    upon by the Senate soon. If it is enacted, negotiations should proceed rapidly
                    towards definite agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
